1. minikube start --driver=docker --cpus=3 --memory=6gb --nodes=3 -p dev-cluster 

2. kubeclt get nodes -o wide

3. kubectl describe node hub-cluster-m02

4. Kubernetes scheduler automatically places Pods on available worker nodes.
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-deploy
spec:
  replicas: 3
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80

4.1 kubectl apply -f nginx.yaml

5. kubectl get pods -o wide

6. Forcing Workloads onto Specific Nodes (Production Concepts)
6.1 Node Labels
Label nodes:
kubectl label node hub-cluster-m02 role=backend
kubectl label node hub-cluster-m03 role=frontend

Use nodeSelector:
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    role: backend


